LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - ASIA (15): MONGOLIA, CATTLE, FIRST REPORT, OIE
*******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 7 Sep 2021
Source: OIE WAHIS [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=39126


Lumpy skin disease [LSD], Mongolia
----------------------------------
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Started: [21 Aug 2021]
Confirmed: [26 Aug 2021]
Reported: 7 Sep 2021
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence in the country
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (3)
[Since 21 Aug 2021, 3 outbreaks of lumpy skin disease (LSD) have occurred in the counties of Chuluunkhoroot, Dashbalbar and Gurvanzagal, all in the province of Dornod. The disease is affecting 3 separate cattle farms. See details of each outbreak at the source URL above. - Mod.CRD]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks (3)
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 197 / 8 / - / 2 / - / -

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures: Disinfection, movement control inside the country, quarantine, selective killing and disposal

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: State central veterinary laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Outbreaks / Test date / Result
Cattle / Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 3 / 26 Aug 2021 / Positive
Cattle / Enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 1 / 26 Aug 2021 / Positive

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

["LSD was first reported in Asia and the Pacific region in 2019 in northwest China, Bangladesh and India. During the northern summer of 2020, LSD has continued its spread across continental Asia with many members in south and south east Asia confirming outbreaks."

"Since 2019, several outbreaks of LSD have been reported by...Bangladesh, India, China, [Taiwan], Viet Nam, Bhutan, Hong Kong (SAR-RPC), Nepal, Sri Lanka, Myanmar, Thailand, Cambodia, [Malaysia and Laos]."

Detailed information summarizing relevant information on the activities that the Asia and Pacific region have been working on, as well as OIE recommendations on LSD, is available at https://rr-asia.oie.int/en/projects/lumpy-skin-disease-lsd/. - Mod.CRD

